# pg-game

Minimal 2D game starter project.

## Description
A small, extensible 2D game template intended as a starting point for rapid prototyping and learning. Built with Python and Pygame (or swap in your preferred engine).

## Features
- Simple game loop
- Sprite and input handling
- Basic collision and scoring
- Configurable settings for quick iteration

## Prerequisites
- Python 3.8+
- pip

## Installation
1. Clone the repository
    git clone <repo-url> pg-game
2. Install dependencies
    pip install -r requirements.txt

## Running
From the project root:
python -m pg_game.main
(or)
python run.py

## Project structure
- pg_game/         — package source
  - main.py        — entry point
  - assets/        — images, sounds
  - config.py      — game settings
  - scenes/        — game states/screens
- tests/           — unit and integration tests
- requirements.txt
- README            — this file

## Development
- Follow PEP8 style
- Run tests: pytest
- Use feature branches and open PRs

## Contributing
Open issues for bugs or features. Keep changes small and documented.

